WEBVTT

00:07.268 --> 00:09.270
- Did you already pack
my kangaroo sweatshirt?

00:09.313 --> 00:11.576
- You're not wearing that.
- Jason said I had to.

00:11.620 --> 00:14.666
- Remember the time you let
Jason talk you into buying a--

00:16.799 --> 00:18.627
- You okay?

00:18.670 --> 00:21.760
- [gagging]

00:21.804 --> 00:24.763
[retches]

00:27.375 --> 00:29.029
- I'll text Jason,
tell him we can't make it.

00:29.072 --> 00:34.077
- No, one of us has to show up,
and I'll be okay.

00:34.121 --> 00:37.689
Mm, morning sickness,
what a crock.

00:39.778 --> 00:44.957
- Well, it's morningsomewhere in the world.

00:45.001 --> 00:47.221
[pop music]

00:47.264 --> 00:48.918
[indistinct chatter]

00:48.961 --> 00:49.962
- [sighs]

00:50.006 --> 00:52.008
I don't knowwhat else we can do.

00:52.052 --> 00:54.097
- Go public.
Make a stink.

00:54.141 --> 00:55.620
Force the cops to do something.

00:55.664 --> 00:57.448
- They said there's nothing
they can do.

00:57.492 --> 00:59.450
They just keep telling me
what I should do.

00:59.494 --> 01:02.584
Get off social media,
change passwords,

01:02.627 --> 01:05.108
oh, live the rest of my life
and Carly's

01:05.152 --> 01:06.631
looking over our shoulder.

01:06.675 --> 01:08.807
- Where's Carly?

01:08.851 --> 01:11.245
- Home--feeling crappy.
She said to say sorry.

01:11.288 --> 01:12.768
[phone chimes]

01:12.811 --> 01:15.771
[ominous music]

01:15.814 --> 01:20.123
♪

01:20.167 --> 01:21.124
- What?

01:21.168 --> 01:23.387
♪

01:23.431 --> 01:24.910
[phone ringing]

01:24.954 --> 01:27.261
- This is Carly.
Sorry I missed your call.

01:27.304 --> 01:29.219
- Hey--
- Hey, Chris!

01:29.263 --> 01:31.656
[indistinct chatter]

01:31.700 --> 01:33.876
- I wait for you, see?Like you say.

01:33.919 --> 01:37.140
[tires screeching]

01:37.184 --> 01:39.186
[gunshots]

01:39.229 --> 01:41.753
- Wait, wait, wait.

01:41.797 --> 01:44.843
[screaming

01:44.887 --> 01:48.325
- Holy--oh, my God!
- Okay, okay, okay.

01:48.369 --> 01:50.806
- Yo, call the police!
- Oh, my God, Jason!

01:50.849 --> 01:52.286
[tires squealing]
- Call the police!

01:52.329 --> 01:54.679
- [panicked breathing]

01:54.723 --> 01:57.029
♪

01:57.073 --> 02:00.032
[tense music]

02:00.076 --> 02:03.514
♪

02:03.558 --> 02:06.300
- CID's throwing usa real curve ball.

02:06.343 --> 02:07.823
- What the hell?

02:07.866 --> 02:11.174
- We're operating undera John Doe fugitive warrant.

02:11.218 --> 02:12.523
The unknown assailant
is wanted

02:12.567 --> 02:14.308
for double homicide
and attempted kidnapping

02:14.351 --> 02:15.918
last night in Brooklyn.

02:15.961 --> 02:18.355
[soft dramatic music]

02:18.399 --> 02:20.444
- Anybody get the plates
from the van?

02:20.488 --> 02:23.186
- No,
the intended kidnap victim

02:23.230 --> 02:24.448
is Chris Thompson,

02:24.492 --> 02:26.407
marketing wonk
in the tech field.

02:26.450 --> 02:29.018
For the past four months,
Thompson has been the target

02:29.061 --> 02:32.195
of a cyberstalker who goes
by the name of HuntingChris.

02:32.239 --> 02:35.807
Two hours before the assault,
Thompson received this text.

02:35.851 --> 02:36.939
♪

02:36.982 --> 02:38.549
- "You won't be
so lucky next time."

02:38.593 --> 02:39.768
Where did
this threat originate?

02:39.811 --> 02:41.378
- Unknown,
but across state lines,

02:41.422 --> 02:42.597
which makes it ours.

02:42.640 --> 02:44.338
It came from behind a VPN

02:44.381 --> 02:46.166
and through
an encrypted server

02:46.209 --> 02:47.471
then bounced
around four states

02:47.515 --> 02:48.864
before it landed
on Thompson's phone.

02:48.907 --> 02:50.692
- Our stalker
knows what he's doing.

02:50.735 --> 02:53.173
- We have any other messages
from him?

02:53.216 --> 02:56.741
- From the police file
when Thompson filed a report

02:56.785 --> 02:59.135
three months ago.
This is the first message.

02:59.179 --> 03:00.397
♪

03:00.441 --> 03:02.747
- "You take my time,
I take yours."

03:02.791 --> 03:04.096
Any more?

03:04.140 --> 03:11.278
♪

03:14.672 --> 03:16.500
- Then last night,
before the assault,

03:16.544 --> 03:18.415
Thompson received this.

03:18.459 --> 03:19.764
"Moving won't help.

03:19.808 --> 03:22.071
I can get to you anywhere--
all three of you."

03:22.114 --> 03:23.420
Thompson's wife's pregnant.

03:23.464 --> 03:24.987
- Stalker's been smart enough

03:25.030 --> 03:27.119
not to make
an actionable threat.

03:27.163 --> 03:29.513
- Well, anybody
this obsessive is dangerous.

03:29.557 --> 03:30.949
The police shouldn't have
had to have two people die

03:30.993 --> 03:31.994
to figure that out.

03:32.037 --> 03:34.475
♪

03:34.518 --> 03:35.911
- Point taken.

03:35.954 --> 03:37.782
It's unclear
what kind of stalker

03:37.826 --> 03:39.262
we're dealing with,
but I think we can eliminate

03:39.306 --> 03:40.481
a couple of categories.

03:40.524 --> 03:42.570
He doesn't read
as an intimacy seeker

03:42.613 --> 03:45.312
nor as an incompetent suitor,
the type who imagine

03:45.355 --> 03:46.965
a loving relationship
with their target.

03:47.009 --> 03:48.663
That leaves
the rejected, resentful,

03:48.706 --> 03:51.579
and the predatory type.

03:51.622 --> 03:53.276
- Thompson and his wife
are in a safe house--

03:53.320 --> 03:54.973
Three shifts, two agents per.

03:55.017 --> 03:58.020
- That bar Thompson
came out of, I know it.

03:58.063 --> 04:01.415
It's upscale, and there's limos
parked outside all the time.

04:01.458 --> 04:04.026
Limos have cameras
in front and back.

04:04.069 --> 04:05.288
- You and Kenny get on that.

04:05.332 --> 04:06.898
We'll take care
of the Thompsons.

04:06.942 --> 04:09.640
Remember, as long as there's
no face on this poster,

04:09.684 --> 04:11.642
the stalker has the upper hand.

04:11.686 --> 04:13.078
A threat
can come from anywhere.

04:13.122 --> 04:16.299
♪

04:16.343 --> 04:19.171
- I have been racking my brain
these last four months

04:19.215 --> 04:21.609
to figure out what I did
to piss this guy off.

04:21.652 --> 04:24.438
Now he's killed my friend
and that poor driver

04:24.481 --> 04:26.440
over something
I don't even know I did.

04:26.483 --> 04:28.355
I don't understand
why he didn't kill me.

04:28.398 --> 04:30.357
I'm the one he's been stalking.

04:30.400 --> 04:31.923
- We don't know for sure
other than

04:31.967 --> 04:34.317
he feels aggrieved by you
and wants to extract an apology

04:34.361 --> 04:35.797
on his terms.

04:35.840 --> 04:37.581
- I have apologized to him.

04:37.625 --> 04:41.019
I even offered to meet him
and talk it out.

04:41.063 --> 04:43.457
- Some stalkers can be
successfully confronted

04:43.500 --> 04:45.502
with the consequences
of their stalking.

04:45.546 --> 04:47.025
Obviously not this one.

04:47.069 --> 04:50.681
- He has sent thousands
of emails to us,

04:50.725 --> 04:53.075
our friends, families,
coworkers.

04:53.118 --> 04:55.512
- And he even sentplumbers and contractors

04:55.556 --> 04:57.340
to our apartmentat all hours of the night.

04:57.384 --> 05:00.343
And the police said that therewas nothing that they could do.

05:00.387 --> 05:01.605
- They can't trace him.

05:01.649 --> 05:03.564
- Okay, so take us through
what happened

05:03.607 --> 05:05.870
in the days before
you got the first message.

05:05.914 --> 05:07.524
- We had dinner
at Carly's parents.

05:07.568 --> 05:09.352
- And then we wentto the paint store

05:09.396 --> 05:10.875
to look for colorsfor the baby's room,

05:10.919 --> 05:13.530
and then we hadan emergency appointment

05:13.574 --> 05:16.185
at my OBGYNbecause I was having pains.

05:17.665 --> 05:21.059
- I went to work.
There's nothing--nothing.

05:21.103 --> 05:24.367
- Well, the message he sent you
before you were attacked

05:24.411 --> 05:26.064
mentioned you were moving?

05:26.108 --> 05:29.372
- I put in for a transfer
to the San Francisco office,

05:29.416 --> 05:32.506
and he knows that.
How does he know?

05:32.549 --> 05:35.335
- Cyberstalkers
can be very tech savvy.

05:35.378 --> 05:36.553
We want to put trackers
on all your devices...

05:36.597 --> 05:38.163
[phone chimes]

05:38.207 --> 05:40.557
So we can see incoming messages
and trace them in real time.

05:40.601 --> 05:43.473
- He's never gonnaleave us alone, is he?

05:43.517 --> 05:44.735
♪

05:44.779 --> 05:46.215
- Sometimes they get tired
of the game,

05:46.258 --> 05:47.564
choose another target.

05:47.608 --> 05:50.262
♪

05:50.306 --> 05:51.394
Sometimes.

05:51.438 --> 05:53.265
♪

05:53.309 --> 05:55.398
- Clinton got a hit
off the limo footage.

05:55.442 --> 05:59.271
♪

05:59.315 --> 06:00.534
- You're safe here.

06:00.577 --> 06:03.058
You follow our direction,
you'll stay safe.

06:03.101 --> 06:05.408
If it's any comfort,

06:05.452 --> 06:07.584
people who are ruled
by their obsessions,

06:07.628 --> 06:10.674
they take risks,
they make mistakes.

06:10.718 --> 06:12.720
We'll catch this person.

06:12.763 --> 06:15.113
- Plate tracks
to an address in Queens.

06:15.157 --> 06:18.421
♪

06:18.465 --> 06:19.988
- It's okay, honey.
It's okay.

06:20.031 --> 06:22.294
- I don't have any guns
in the house, I swear.

06:22.338 --> 06:23.557
I have kids.

06:23.600 --> 06:26.560
- Just a sedan
in the garage--no van.

06:26.603 --> 06:29.345
- Your green van,
Mr. Upton, where is it?

06:29.389 --> 06:30.694
[indistinct radio chatter]

06:30.738 --> 06:34.132
- I sold it a couple weeks ago
to some guy.

06:34.176 --> 06:37.832
- This guy have a name?
- I--I don't remember it.

06:37.875 --> 06:40.791
- It'll be on the transfer
of ownership papers.

06:40.835 --> 06:42.489
[indistinct radio chatter]

06:42.532 --> 06:44.621
- So you don't havethe transfer papers.

06:44.665 --> 06:46.449
You wanna tell us
another story?

06:46.493 --> 06:47.798
- [sighs]
This is scary.

06:47.842 --> 06:51.280
I--I don't know
who has the van.

06:53.413 --> 06:56.938
No, really, I advertised it
online, and this...

06:58.200 --> 07:01.246
This creep got
in touch with me online.

07:03.074 --> 07:04.424
[sighs]

07:04.467 --> 07:06.251
He hacked
into my computer's camera

07:06.295 --> 07:09.211
and filmed me watching--

07:09.254 --> 07:11.343
watching porn.

07:11.387 --> 07:12.475
- Not a crime.

07:12.519 --> 07:13.955
- Yeah, maybe not for you.

07:13.998 --> 07:15.696
My wife would kill me
if she found out.

07:15.739 --> 07:17.828
- Anyone ever tell you
to cover up the camera?

07:17.872 --> 07:19.482
- Well, I have now.

07:19.526 --> 07:21.528
- The van, Mr. Upton.

07:21.571 --> 07:23.051
- The creep told me
where to leave it--

07:23.094 --> 07:25.662
in New Jersey in the middle
of nowhere at night--

07:25.706 --> 07:28.622
or he would send
his video of me

07:28.665 --> 07:31.015
to my wife, my sister,
whoever else I knew

07:31.059 --> 07:32.626
'cause he had my contact list.

07:32.669 --> 07:34.279
I did what he said.

07:34.323 --> 07:35.716
I let him steal my van.

07:35.759 --> 07:37.108
- And did you see himor talk to him?

07:37.152 --> 07:39.937
- No, but he was somewhere.
He was watching.

07:39.981 --> 07:41.461
I walked away
like he told me to,

07:41.504 --> 07:44.594
but I looked back, and he
sent me a text right away.

07:44.638 --> 07:46.117
Told me to keep walking
to the corner

07:46.161 --> 07:48.511
and get on
the 107 bus or else.

07:48.555 --> 07:50.382
♪

07:50.426 --> 07:53.429
- This place makes the middle
of nowhere sound exotic.

07:53.473 --> 07:55.431
- It's a perfect
drop off place--

07:55.475 --> 07:56.911
hidden from the street,

07:56.954 --> 07:59.653
behind businesses
that are closed at night.

07:59.696 --> 08:01.437
- Only someonewho knows the neighborhood

08:01.481 --> 08:04.309
would know about it.
- Knows about the 107 bus too.

08:04.353 --> 08:07.095
- Our John Doe either works
or lives around here.

08:07.138 --> 08:09.358
- Upton walked back down
to the road

08:09.401 --> 08:11.839
after he dropped the van.

08:11.882 --> 08:13.754
Our John Doewas watching him.

08:13.797 --> 08:15.799
Could be any oneof those buildings or houses.

08:15.843 --> 08:19.542
♪

08:19.586 --> 08:20.804
- Could be watching us
right now.

08:20.848 --> 08:22.719
♪

08:22.763 --> 08:24.982
- We need to canvass
the entire neighborhood.

08:25.026 --> 08:27.289
Check for the van,
security cameras

08:27.332 --> 08:29.639
all the way from hereto the top of the Heights.

08:29.683 --> 08:35.036
♪

08:35.079 --> 08:36.994
- The nearest working
security camera

08:37.038 --> 08:38.909
was a quarter milefrom that lot.

08:38.953 --> 08:40.955
No sign of the green vanheading south.

08:40.998 --> 08:43.479
- Or north--he's probably
heading east

08:43.523 --> 08:46.264
up into the Heights.
It's residential, no cameras.

08:46.308 --> 08:48.179
- Canvass hasn't
turned up anything.

08:48.223 --> 08:50.051
- And the texts Upton gotafter he left the van

08:50.094 --> 08:52.314
trace to a single use burner,so our John Doe

08:52.357 --> 08:54.403
used it only
to communicate with Upton.

08:54.446 --> 08:55.578
He hasn't used it since.

08:55.622 --> 08:57.319
- He is disciplined.

08:57.362 --> 08:59.582
- Shopping
for serial killer vans?

08:59.626 --> 09:01.149
No windows.

09:01.192 --> 09:04.587
- These are the photos
Upton posted on Craigslist.

09:04.631 --> 09:06.241
- He kept the vanin good shape.

09:06.284 --> 09:08.373
- That he does.
[phone chimes]

09:08.417 --> 09:10.288
Hana, can you pull up
the pictures of the van

09:10.332 --> 09:11.812
on the night of the shooting?
- Mm-hmm.

09:11.855 --> 09:14.292
♪

09:14.336 --> 09:15.380
Nice try, jerk.

09:15.424 --> 09:16.904
♪

09:16.947 --> 09:18.949
- Problem?
- Nope.

09:18.993 --> 09:20.734
I've got the photos right here.

09:20.777 --> 09:21.952
♪

09:21.996 --> 09:24.215
- I'll need
a side by side comparison.

09:24.259 --> 09:25.695
- I can do that.

09:26.653 --> 09:29.743
- You see the dings
in the panel here and here?

09:29.786 --> 09:31.527
They weren't there
when Upton was selling it.

09:31.571 --> 09:33.877
- Those are the kind of marks
you get in a parking lot

09:33.921 --> 09:35.618
when someone next to you
dings you with their door.

09:35.662 --> 09:37.098
- You're right.

09:37.141 --> 09:38.926
Our John Doe's been keeping it
in a public parking lot.

09:38.969 --> 09:40.710
Now, he's gonna try it again.

09:40.754 --> 09:43.800
To kidnap Thompson,
he'll need a van.

09:43.844 --> 09:45.628
- He has to figure
we made the plates.

09:45.672 --> 09:46.890
The van's hot.

09:46.934 --> 09:48.457
He probably ditched it
and got a new one.

09:48.500 --> 09:50.720
- Yeah, but he went to a lot
of trouble to get that one.

09:50.764 --> 09:52.417
Be easierjust to switch the plates.

09:52.461 --> 09:54.681
- And park it somewhere
you won't draw attention.

09:54.724 --> 09:57.771
- Or get towed.
- Won't get tickets.

09:57.814 --> 10:00.425
- Hana, take us down
Tonnele Avenue.

10:00.469 --> 10:02.166
- Fasten your seat belts.

10:02.210 --> 10:08.999
♪

10:09.043 --> 10:10.784
- It's all private lots.
There's nowhere to hide.

10:10.827 --> 10:12.655
- Keep going.

10:12.699 --> 10:14.483
♪

10:14.526 --> 10:15.658
Stop.

10:15.702 --> 10:17.181
♪

10:17.225 --> 10:20.184
Now, what is that right there?

10:20.228 --> 10:23.231
- Newark Airport
long-term parking.

10:23.274 --> 10:24.449
♪

10:24.493 --> 10:25.668
- All right.

10:25.712 --> 10:27.801
[dramatic music]

10:27.844 --> 10:29.890
- Stand back.
Lead team on approach.

10:29.933 --> 10:31.326
- Now hold that.
Hold that.

10:31.369 --> 10:34.155
♪

10:34.198 --> 10:35.373
- Clear!

10:35.417 --> 10:41.205
♪

10:41.249 --> 10:42.598
- Clear!

10:42.642 --> 10:44.208
- Oh, my God.

10:44.252 --> 10:45.383
♪

10:45.427 --> 10:47.690
- Restraints
for stress positions,

10:47.734 --> 10:49.561
bone breaking tools.

10:49.605 --> 10:50.911
- Dungeon on wheels.

10:50.954 --> 10:52.173
♪

10:52.216 --> 10:53.783
- It hurts just looking at it.

10:53.827 --> 10:56.873
- The guy who would build this,he'll never stop.

10:56.917 --> 10:58.875
♪

11:04.533 --> 11:06.100
- All right, it's all yours.

11:06.143 --> 11:09.277
- So he wants to immobilize
Thompson spread eagle face up,

11:09.320 --> 11:11.105
and he wants Thompson
to be able to see him.

11:11.148 --> 11:13.847
- To watch him take the tools
of the trade off the rack.

11:13.890 --> 11:16.719
- Anticipation
is part of the terror.

11:16.763 --> 11:18.416
- Any volunteers?

11:18.460 --> 11:21.724
We need somebody with roughly
the same size head as Thompson.

11:21.768 --> 11:24.292
- Uh, that would be you, boss.
- Definitely.

11:24.335 --> 11:26.686
You could share hats.

11:26.729 --> 11:29.906
- I'll hold your hand.
- [chuckles]

11:31.081 --> 11:33.605
All right then.
Help me out here.

11:45.922 --> 11:48.185
Okay,
so it's not very comfortable.

11:48.229 --> 11:51.145
It's tight on my head,
and I can't really move my jaw.

11:51.188 --> 11:53.669
Actually--yeah, yeah, get--

11:56.106 --> 11:57.368
Ugh.

11:57.412 --> 11:59.806
Well, everything else
is off the shelf,

11:59.849 --> 12:02.243
but this head cage
is custom fit, handmade.

12:02.286 --> 12:03.548
[phone chimes]

12:03.592 --> 12:04.767
- By someone who knows
what they're doing.

12:04.811 --> 12:06.943
No rough edges,
joints are clean--

12:06.987 --> 12:10.120
probably a craftsman who
caters to the bondage crowd.

12:10.164 --> 12:12.340
- Let's find him.

12:12.383 --> 12:14.255
- If Thompson only knew

12:14.298 --> 12:15.604
what this sick puppy
had in mind for him.

12:15.647 --> 12:16.605
[soft dramatic music]

12:16.648 --> 12:18.520
- He'll find out.
People talk.

12:18.563 --> 12:20.174
- We should be the ones
to tell them.

12:20.217 --> 12:21.741
- All right, you up for it?

12:21.784 --> 12:23.351
You seem to have a good rapportwith the Thompsons.

12:23.394 --> 12:24.395
- Mm-hmm.

12:24.439 --> 12:25.614
♪

12:25.657 --> 12:27.094
- I think
I should go too, boss.

12:27.137 --> 12:30.184
It's gonna be traumatic.
I can do trauma.

12:30.227 --> 12:31.663
♪

12:31.707 --> 12:32.708
- Okay.

12:32.752 --> 12:35.842
♪

12:35.885 --> 12:37.582
- You can't let anybody
bully you.

12:37.626 --> 12:39.976
Just 'cause they think
they're God almighty

12:40.020 --> 12:41.499
doesn't mean
you have to take their crap.

12:41.543 --> 12:45.895
You gotta hit 'em like this
and this and this!

12:45.939 --> 12:48.898
[ominous music]

12:48.942 --> 12:50.770
That's the one.

12:50.813 --> 12:52.859
♪

12:52.902 --> 12:54.861
That's the one for him.

12:54.904 --> 12:57.602
♪

12:57.646 --> 12:58.995
[grunts]

12:59.039 --> 13:01.302
- Hold me captive in a van?

13:01.345 --> 13:03.826
And do what to me?
- Nothing pleasant.

13:03.870 --> 13:06.220
He had restraints
and other things to hurt you.

13:06.263 --> 13:07.569
- Oh, my God.

13:07.612 --> 13:09.223
- But none of that
is going to happen now.

13:09.266 --> 13:10.354
- How do you know?

13:10.398 --> 13:12.182
He could just disappear,
couldn't he?

13:12.226 --> 13:15.359
Until you and everybody else
lose interest, and then--

13:15.403 --> 13:17.492
- I won't lose interest.
- None of us will.

13:17.535 --> 13:19.233
Once we put someone
on the most wanted list,

13:19.276 --> 13:22.366
they stay there until
they're caught or they're dead.

13:22.410 --> 13:24.368
- Oh, well--

13:24.412 --> 13:26.109
- How are we supposedto live until then?

13:26.153 --> 13:27.632
- Keeping busy helps.

13:27.676 --> 13:28.851
You'd be surprised how quickly

13:28.895 --> 13:30.766
being vigilant
becomes second nature.

13:30.810 --> 13:33.290
You'll discover
the remarkable human ability

13:33.334 --> 13:34.596
to deal with terrible things

13:34.639 --> 13:37.033
such as fear, disease,
and robocalls.

13:37.077 --> 13:38.861
- And talking helps too.

13:38.905 --> 13:40.863
Now, you've been
through some trauma,

13:40.907 --> 13:45.259
and that can manifest
mood swings, bad sleep.

13:45.302 --> 13:46.521
We can put you
in touch with people

13:46.564 --> 13:48.175
who can help you sort it out,

13:48.218 --> 13:49.567
and it's really worth doing.

13:49.611 --> 13:51.743
[soft dramatic music]

13:51.787 --> 13:53.441
- We thought
we could just run away.

13:53.484 --> 13:56.966
♪

13:57.010 --> 13:59.273
He's gonna outlast us.

13:59.316 --> 14:01.710
He's stronger than us,
and he's focused.

14:01.753 --> 14:03.755
He's got nothing else
in his life

14:03.799 --> 14:05.932
except for this senseless hate
for me!

14:05.975 --> 14:08.238
♪

14:08.282 --> 14:10.240
- [sighs]

14:10.284 --> 14:12.112
I'm losing him.

14:12.155 --> 14:13.635
♪

14:13.678 --> 14:15.985
We're having a baby,
and I'm losing my husband.

14:16.029 --> 14:20.207
♪

14:20.250 --> 14:22.296
- [sighs]

14:22.339 --> 14:23.906
♪

14:23.950 --> 14:25.647
- Not too far
from Hawthorn, actually.

14:25.690 --> 14:27.475
- Oh, is that right?

14:27.518 --> 14:28.824
- I don't know about him,

14:28.868 --> 14:30.304
but I think she connectedwith what you told them.

14:30.347 --> 14:32.741
- Yeah?
Maybe.

14:33.829 --> 14:35.091
- You go in.

14:35.135 --> 14:36.223
I'm gonna stay out hereand get some fresh air.

14:36.266 --> 14:38.399
- All right.

14:38.442 --> 14:39.661
[sighs]

14:39.704 --> 14:42.882
Hey, is there anythingyou want to tell me?

14:44.187 --> 14:46.146
- About what?

14:46.189 --> 14:47.712
- I don't know.

14:47.756 --> 14:51.107
It's like this case landedon you like a ton of bricks--

14:51.151 --> 14:53.414
and those text messagesyou've been getting...

14:55.155 --> 14:56.460
- It's nothing, Kenny.

14:56.504 --> 14:59.115
Thanks for asking.

15:06.862 --> 15:08.951
[sighs]

15:12.737 --> 15:14.522
- Has Hana done
a stalker case before?

15:14.565 --> 15:16.393
Maybe one that went south?

15:17.612 --> 15:19.092
- Why do you ask?

15:23.531 --> 15:25.663
Where is she?

15:25.707 --> 15:28.623
[tense music]

15:28.666 --> 15:34.324
♪

15:34.368 --> 15:35.935
I realize this case
is dredging up

15:35.978 --> 15:37.675
bad memories for you,
but I thought you'd be able

15:37.719 --> 15:39.851
to harness them to good effect.

15:39.895 --> 15:41.505
Was I wrong?

15:42.767 --> 15:45.596
- It's not the memories.

15:45.640 --> 15:52.777
♪

15:59.654 --> 16:02.135
A few years ago,
before I knew all of you,

16:02.178 --> 16:04.528
there was a guy, Jack Wellman,

16:04.572 --> 16:08.576
a hacker, an FBI contractor.

16:08.619 --> 16:11.492
We went on a date,
by which I mean one.

16:11.535 --> 16:13.581
The chemistry
wasn't right for me.

16:13.624 --> 16:16.192
Well, that wasn't good enoughfor Mr. Wellman.

16:16.236 --> 16:17.759
He started stalking me.

16:17.802 --> 16:21.458
Emails, texts, turning upat my apartment

16:21.502 --> 16:23.547
all hoursof the day and night,

16:23.591 --> 16:26.289
sending me flowers and gifts.
- Hana--

16:26.333 --> 16:28.944
- He didn't break the law,
but I reported him,

16:28.988 --> 16:30.598
and he was fired
from the bureau.

16:30.641 --> 16:32.600
- Is he still harassing you?

16:32.643 --> 16:35.516
- He lets me know
he's around.

16:35.559 --> 16:37.605
He makes me feel weak
and vulnerable,

16:37.648 --> 16:40.260
and I don't like it.

16:40.303 --> 16:42.566
I hadn't heard from him
for about six months,

16:42.610 --> 16:45.439
but he's resurfaced
offering help.

16:45.482 --> 16:47.615
He says he knows
something about our guy.

16:47.658 --> 16:50.226
He could full of crap,
but he's a great hacker--

16:50.270 --> 16:52.620
better than our John Doe.
- What does he want in return?

16:52.663 --> 16:56.102
- To meet me--
just the two of us.

16:56.145 --> 16:57.886
♪

16:57.929 --> 16:59.583
- [sighs]

16:59.627 --> 17:00.845
- It's out of the question.

17:00.889 --> 17:05.024
- Wait, hold on.
That's up to Hana, isn't it?

17:05.067 --> 17:08.636
- It is up to me,
and I'm not sure.

17:08.679 --> 17:10.986
- This just came in.

17:11.030 --> 17:14.120
We got a hit on the welder
who made the head cage.

17:14.163 --> 17:17.123
♪

17:17.166 --> 17:18.820
- Who said I made it?

17:18.863 --> 17:20.213
- We do.

17:20.256 --> 17:22.302
- And so do the people
at the Marquis Sex Shop

17:22.345 --> 17:23.694
who sell your goods.

17:23.738 --> 17:26.001
They recognize
your craftsmanship.

17:26.045 --> 17:28.482
- We wanna knowwho you made this piece for.

17:28.525 --> 17:30.092
- I make a lot of these.

17:30.136 --> 17:31.528
All sorts of people

17:31.572 --> 17:33.095
like a little discipline
in their lives.

17:33.139 --> 17:34.966
You'd be surprised.
- I wouldn't.

17:35.010 --> 17:38.709
- This would've been made
custom fit for somebody.

17:40.407 --> 17:41.973
Maybe you can check

17:42.017 --> 17:43.932
your dimensions
against the records.

17:43.975 --> 17:46.065
- I could if I kept records.

17:46.108 --> 17:48.763
- No records of
cash transactions or checks?

17:48.806 --> 17:50.634
- I don't think money
was involved here.

17:50.678 --> 17:51.853
♪

17:51.896 --> 17:53.463
Isn't that right, Mr. Royce?

17:53.507 --> 17:55.683
♪

17:55.726 --> 17:57.685
The man we're after
has a preferred method

17:57.728 --> 18:00.035
of getting what he wants--
blackmail.

18:00.079 --> 18:01.776
♪

18:01.819 --> 18:04.692
Let's say he hacked
into a camera security system

18:04.735 --> 18:06.868
and caught somebody
doing something dicey

18:06.911 --> 18:10.176
like illegal safe cracking.

18:10.219 --> 18:12.221
♪

18:12.265 --> 18:15.703
- Acme Strong,
they make good safes.

18:15.746 --> 18:17.705
- Nothing a talented welder
couldn't open.

18:17.748 --> 18:19.141
♪

18:19.185 --> 18:21.056
Now you're gonna tell us
that you crack safes

18:21.100 --> 18:23.711
for the legal owners
who forget their combinations.

18:23.754 --> 18:25.408
- Sounds about right.

18:25.452 --> 18:27.149
- I wonder if the NYPD
would agree.

18:27.193 --> 18:29.804
What do you think, Barnes?
- You know what?

18:29.847 --> 18:32.981
They love arresting people,especially when somebody else

18:33.024 --> 18:34.417
just hands them the evidence.

18:34.461 --> 18:37.159
- So this guywho ordered the cage,

18:37.203 --> 18:40.554
he has a tape on you crackinga safe, and he blackmailed you.

18:40.597 --> 18:42.251
♪

18:42.295 --> 18:43.426
- Yeah.

18:43.470 --> 18:47.343
Okay, if you put it that way...

18:47.387 --> 18:48.910
He sent me the dimensions.

18:48.953 --> 18:50.651
He told me to leave the piece
at some God forsaken place

18:50.694 --> 18:53.436
out in Union City.

18:53.480 --> 18:54.916
- Tonnele Avenue.

18:54.959 --> 18:57.179
- Gee, I didn't know
it was such a hot spot.

18:57.223 --> 18:59.225
- You happen to geta look at him maybe?

18:59.268 --> 19:00.748
♪

19:00.791 --> 19:02.750
I doubled back and hid.

19:02.793 --> 19:05.492
I wanted to see
the little pissant.

19:05.535 --> 19:08.712
That's him, and that's his car.

19:08.756 --> 19:11.585
♪

19:11.628 --> 19:14.544
[suspenseful music]

19:14.588 --> 19:17.547
♪

19:17.591 --> 19:18.592
- Clear.

19:18.635 --> 19:22.248
♪

19:22.291 --> 19:23.510
- Clear in back!

19:23.553 --> 19:25.425
- Clear!

19:25.468 --> 19:28.993
♪

19:29.037 --> 19:30.430
- Clear.

19:30.473 --> 19:32.171
- Main floor clear!

19:32.214 --> 19:35.348
[dramatic music]

19:35.391 --> 19:38.568
- Welcome to stalking central.

19:38.612 --> 19:42.224
♪

19:42.268 --> 19:45.445
- Camera's on.
He's watching us.

19:45.488 --> 19:48.926
♪

19:48.970 --> 19:50.798
- Let's get the CART team
in here

19:50.841 --> 19:52.191
before we tear
this place apart.

19:52.234 --> 19:54.758
♪

19:54.802 --> 19:57.587
- Can you trace his location?

19:57.631 --> 19:59.937
♪

19:59.981 --> 20:02.331
- Coffee shop on Chestnut.

20:02.375 --> 20:04.899
♪

20:04.942 --> 20:06.857
- Too late, suckers.

20:06.901 --> 20:11.297
♪

20:11.340 --> 20:12.733
[sighs]

20:12.776 --> 20:14.735
♪

20:14.778 --> 20:16.954
[laughter]

20:16.998 --> 20:19.043
- Seems pleased with himself.

20:19.087 --> 20:20.567
- Four sugars with his coffee--

20:20.610 --> 20:21.916
I hope his teeth rotout of his head.

20:21.959 --> 20:24.440
♪

20:29.271 --> 20:31.708
- David Fallon of Newark
has been identified

20:31.752 --> 20:33.754
as a suspect
in a double homicide

20:33.797 --> 20:35.234
and attempted kidnapping

20:35.277 --> 20:36.844
last Tuesday night
in Brooklyn.

20:36.887 --> 20:38.411
- Take a look at this.

20:38.454 --> 20:40.848
- Fallon, a self-employed
security systems installer

20:40.891 --> 20:43.503
lived alone
here in this house--

20:43.546 --> 20:47.071
- "Didn't hold the elevator,
blocked the alley entrance,

20:47.115 --> 20:51.075
cut in line, didn't apologize
for knocking over my coffee."

20:51.119 --> 20:52.990
- Everyone
who's ever offended him--

20:53.034 --> 20:56.298
times, dates,
description of the offender.

20:56.342 --> 20:59.997
- Thin skinned little bastard.
- Check this out.

21:00.998 --> 21:02.783
- Broken taillight?

21:02.826 --> 21:05.916
- By the markings on it,
looks like a Japanese model.

21:05.960 --> 21:08.267
- Fallon started remotely
deleting the hard drives

21:08.310 --> 21:09.659
as soon
as we entered the house.

21:09.703 --> 21:11.226
Not sure how much we saved.

21:11.270 --> 21:14.664
- "September 10, 1993,
7:10 a.m.

21:14.708 --> 21:15.796
"The man left work.

21:15.839 --> 21:17.841
"5:42 p.m.
The man came home.

21:17.885 --> 21:19.626
"8:17.
Man yelled at his wife.

21:19.669 --> 21:22.106
11:06 p.m.
Lights out."

21:22.150 --> 21:24.805
He was watching someone.
- 1993?

21:24.848 --> 21:26.850
Fallon must have beeneight or nine.

21:26.894 --> 21:29.288
- Stalker even then.

21:29.331 --> 21:32.160
- Polaroids,probably taken by a child.

21:32.203 --> 21:33.466
- How much do you have
to piss off an eight-year-old

21:33.509 --> 21:35.990
to make him stalk you?

21:36.033 --> 21:38.340
- I found Fallon's client list,

21:38.384 --> 21:41.256
all the places wherehe installed security systems.

21:41.300 --> 21:43.476
Check this out.

21:43.519 --> 21:45.129
- "Nevins Street Obstetrics."

21:45.173 --> 21:47.001
- Carly Thompson's clinic.

21:47.044 --> 21:48.655
The one they visitedright before

21:48.698 --> 21:50.309
Fallon started stalking them.

21:54.138 --> 21:55.357
- I've never seen himat the clinic.

21:55.401 --> 21:57.403
- You said
you had to see your doctor

21:57.446 --> 21:58.578
because you were in pain?

21:58.621 --> 22:00.231
- Yes, we called ahead.

22:00.275 --> 22:02.843
The receptionisthurried us to the back.

22:02.886 --> 22:05.236
Doctor Gupta was inthe hallway talking to some--

22:05.280 --> 22:07.848
- Him.

22:07.891 --> 22:11.330
She was talking to him.

22:11.373 --> 22:13.027
- Then what happened?

22:13.070 --> 22:15.812
- Nothing.
Dr. Gupta saw us coming.

22:15.856 --> 22:17.858
She broke off the conversation
with this guy

22:17.901 --> 22:19.294
and hustled us
into an exam room.

22:19.338 --> 22:21.383
- Did you say anything to him?
- No.

22:21.427 --> 22:23.559
- Did he react
to being interrupted?

22:23.603 --> 22:24.821
- Not that I noticed.

22:24.865 --> 22:26.345
- Was there
any physical contact?

22:26.388 --> 22:28.347
Maybe you nudged him
or something?

22:28.390 --> 22:30.479
- No, I went around him.

22:30.523 --> 22:32.568
- That's it?

22:32.612 --> 22:33.874
That's why he's doing this?

22:33.917 --> 22:35.354
[soft dramatic music]

22:35.397 --> 22:37.399
I thought I was having
a miscarriage.

22:37.443 --> 22:39.227
Isn't that more important
than whatever

22:39.270 --> 22:41.055
he was talking about
with Dr. Gupta?

22:41.098 --> 22:44.232
- Of course it was...
to a normal person.

22:44.275 --> 22:46.060
♪

22:46.103 --> 22:47.583
- Well, thank youfor this information.

22:47.627 --> 22:48.802
It's been very helpful.

22:48.845 --> 22:50.934
- Now you know who he is.You'll catch him.

22:50.978 --> 22:52.632
♪

22:52.675 --> 22:56.375
- I understand this isn't easy,
but you'll need to be patient.

22:56.418 --> 23:02.293
♪

23:02.337 --> 23:04.905
All these minor slightsand insults,

23:04.948 --> 23:06.472
they're triggering Fallon,reminding him

23:06.515 --> 23:08.430
of a traumatic experience.

23:08.474 --> 23:10.737
- The man in his diary,
the guy across the street,

23:10.780 --> 23:12.086
maybe that's what warped him--

23:12.129 --> 23:13.566
not that it makes me
feel sorry for him.

23:13.609 --> 23:14.567
- You don't have to pity him.

23:14.610 --> 23:15.611
You just haveto understand him.

23:15.655 --> 23:16.743
Where he's beenis where he'll be.

23:16.786 --> 23:18.222
That's how we'll catch him.

23:18.266 --> 23:20.268
- So we're going to find
Fallon's first stalking victim

23:20.311 --> 23:21.487
from 1993.

23:21.530 --> 23:24.490
[dramatic music]

23:24.533 --> 23:25.926
♪

23:25.969 --> 23:27.231
- You know
what he's gonna say--

23:27.275 --> 23:30.191
gonna say he didn't mean it.

23:30.234 --> 23:33.063
He thinks he's so important...

23:33.107 --> 23:35.892
and now you're nothing.

23:35.936 --> 23:37.285
♪

23:37.328 --> 23:39.766
You're gonna break him
into nothing.

23:39.809 --> 23:41.550
♪

23:41.594 --> 23:43.509
[grunts]

23:43.552 --> 23:50.472
♪

23:54.520 --> 23:56.173
- Excuse me.

23:56.217 --> 23:57.958
Can I help you with that?

23:58.001 --> 23:59.220
- Who the hell are you?

23:59.263 --> 24:01.265
- I'm Agent LaCroix of the FBI.

24:01.309 --> 24:03.529
We're looking for information
on a former neighbor of yours--

24:03.572 --> 24:06.096
the Fallons.
They lived across the street.

24:06.140 --> 24:08.751
Mister...
- Tommy Wright.

24:08.795 --> 24:10.492
I see you brought
your girlfriends.

24:10.536 --> 24:13.103
So what do they do,
hold your gun for you?

24:13.147 --> 24:15.584
- We have our own guns.

24:15.628 --> 24:17.281
- Do you remember the Fallons?

24:17.325 --> 24:20.371
- A brood of no account losers.

24:20.415 --> 24:24.506
Now get the hell of my propertybefore I toss you off!

24:24.550 --> 24:26.160
- Dad, what's wrong?

24:26.203 --> 24:29.729
- These morons from the FBI!They're trespassing.

24:29.772 --> 24:31.295
- It's okay, Dad.Go inside.

24:31.339 --> 24:33.646
I'll take care of this.
- All right.

24:33.689 --> 24:36.475
Don't let them push you around.

24:39.782 --> 24:41.697
- I apologize for my father.

24:41.741 --> 24:42.872
- It's all right.

24:42.916 --> 24:45.179
We were asking
about David Fallon.

24:45.222 --> 24:46.659
- He lived across the streetwith his parents.

24:46.702 --> 24:48.138
I saw his name in the news.

24:48.182 --> 24:51.011
- He seemed to have
a fascination with your father.

24:51.054 --> 24:54.231
- He took these pictures.
- Oh, wow.

24:54.275 --> 24:57.408
Well, Dad has a reputationin the neighborhood.

24:57.452 --> 25:00.760
- You mean as a bully?
- I know how he comes off.

25:00.803 --> 25:04.024
- In 1993, Fallon kept
a diary about your father.

25:04.067 --> 25:05.547
Any idea
what might have happened

25:05.591 --> 25:06.722
between the two of them?

25:06.766 --> 25:08.202
- My dad didn't pickon little kids,

25:08.245 --> 25:11.031
but Davey's father,he was fair game.

25:11.074 --> 25:14.904
Mr. Fallon was meek, I guess,kind of sad-looking.

25:14.948 --> 25:17.341
- This was with the Polaroids.

25:17.385 --> 25:19.866
It's from a broken taillight.
Does that mean anything to you?

25:19.909 --> 25:21.128
[soft dramatic music]

25:21.171 --> 25:23.565
- I think so.I was 16.

25:23.609 --> 25:26.220
I remember Mr. Fallonbacking out of his driveway

25:26.263 --> 25:28.570
and Dad pulling into ours.

25:28.614 --> 25:29.919
They bumped into each other.

25:29.963 --> 25:31.442
Mr. Fallon gota broken taillight.

25:31.486 --> 25:34.010
Dad jumped outscreaming at Mr. Fallon

25:34.054 --> 25:36.056
who was apologizing.

25:36.099 --> 25:37.666
Dad slapped him.

25:37.710 --> 25:40.060
Mr. Fallon didn't do anything.

25:40.103 --> 25:42.192
He just got back in his carand drove off.

25:42.236 --> 25:44.064
- And where was David?

25:44.107 --> 25:46.762
- In his front yard.He saw the whole thing.

25:46.806 --> 25:48.459
He lookedlike he was gonna cry.

25:48.503 --> 25:51.854
I felt so bad for Daveyseeing his father humiliated.

25:51.898 --> 25:53.682
♪

25:53.726 --> 25:56.250
- Any other incidents between
your dad and the Fallons?

25:56.293 --> 25:58.905
- No, Mr. Fallon dieda year after.

25:58.948 --> 26:00.341
Heart attack, I heard.

26:00.384 --> 26:02.517
Davey moved away with his mom.

26:02.561 --> 26:04.693
♪

26:04.737 --> 26:08.088
- Found the autopsy report
on Fallon's father--

26:08.131 --> 26:09.916
not a heart attack,
death by suicide.

26:09.959 --> 26:11.918
He swalloweda pesticide cocktail.

26:11.961 --> 26:13.615
His wife found himin the basement.

26:13.659 --> 26:15.008
- She lied to the neighbors

26:15.051 --> 26:16.444
then slipped out of town
with their son.

26:16.487 --> 26:18.446
- I'm sure young Fallondrew a straight line

26:18.489 --> 26:20.666
between the humiliationand his father's death.

26:20.709 --> 26:22.798
- That's a heavy weight
for a kid to carry.

26:22.842 --> 26:23.973
No wonder he gets triggered

26:24.017 --> 26:25.627
every time someone
disrespected him.

26:25.671 --> 26:26.759
- He's not a child anymore.

26:26.802 --> 26:29.631
He's an adult
and grievance collector.

26:29.675 --> 26:30.719
- And a coward.

26:30.763 --> 26:32.112
Some of the people
in his journal,

26:32.155 --> 26:33.635
he slashed their tires,canceled their credit cards.

26:33.679 --> 26:36.072
[phone chimes]
He poisoned a dog.

26:36.116 --> 26:39.641
Escalating but neverconfronting 'em face to face.

26:39.685 --> 26:41.469
- Could be a learned behavior
from his father.

26:41.512 --> 26:44.037
People with depressionlike to avoid confrontation.

26:44.080 --> 26:46.648
Ultimately, that could bewho he's angry with.

26:46.692 --> 26:49.825
- Speaking of cowards,
I just got another text message

26:49.869 --> 26:51.740
from Jack Wellman.

26:51.784 --> 26:54.177
"High fives for IDing Fallon,

26:54.221 --> 26:55.962
but I could've
spared you the trouble."

26:56.005 --> 26:57.659
Look at this.

26:57.703 --> 26:58.965
- He hacked Fallon's phone?

26:59.008 --> 27:00.401
♪

27:00.444 --> 27:02.316
- I told you he was good.

27:02.359 --> 27:04.057
"I have more good stuff
for you.

27:04.100 --> 27:07.190
Let's meet--you and me."

27:07.234 --> 27:09.062
He's offering intel on Fallon.

27:09.105 --> 27:10.716
♪

27:10.759 --> 27:12.282
It can't hurt to hear
what he's got.

27:12.326 --> 27:14.981
- Mm, could hurt you.

27:15.024 --> 27:16.286
- To get a killer
off the street,

27:16.330 --> 27:17.679
I'm willing
to take that chance.

27:17.723 --> 27:21.596
♪

27:21.640 --> 27:23.032
- I'll go with you.

27:23.076 --> 27:25.556
- If it makes you feel better.
Just don't bite him.

27:25.600 --> 27:27.036
♪

27:27.080 --> 27:29.517
[indistinct chatter]

27:29.560 --> 27:36.480
♪

27:40.528 --> 27:42.008
- So...

27:42.051 --> 27:43.662
♪

27:43.705 --> 27:44.837
- What have you got?

27:44.880 --> 27:46.534
- Bad case of you.

27:46.577 --> 27:48.449
♪

27:48.492 --> 27:50.364
- You said you have good stuffon Fallon.

27:50.407 --> 27:53.236
- I do.
I didn't say it comes free.

27:54.237 --> 27:56.283
You never gave me a reason.

27:56.326 --> 27:59.242
- I did give it.You refused to hear it.

27:59.286 --> 28:01.462
♪

28:01.505 --> 28:03.203
So what have you got on Fallon?

28:03.246 --> 28:05.118
You hacked his cell phone.You have his IMSI?

28:05.161 --> 28:06.510
- You know,
if you'd been nice to me,

28:06.554 --> 28:07.860
I could've given you
that photo of him two days ago

28:07.903 --> 28:11.733
before you ID'ed him.
You'd be ahead of the game.

28:11.777 --> 28:14.083
- "Game."

28:14.127 --> 28:16.129
Do you have anything on Fallon?

28:16.172 --> 28:18.697
- There's an easy way
to find out:

28:18.740 --> 28:20.133
us back together.

28:20.176 --> 28:21.395
♪

28:21.438 --> 28:23.005
- We were never together, Jack.

28:23.049 --> 28:25.704
We went on one date, and youdecided I was your property.

28:25.747 --> 28:27.575
Stay away from me.Stop stalking me.

28:27.618 --> 28:29.098
- Stalking?
I'm not stalking--

28:29.142 --> 28:30.230
- Get up off that stool,

28:30.273 --> 28:31.579
you're gonna have
two broken legs.

28:31.622 --> 28:33.320
- What are you,her boyfriend or something?

28:33.363 --> 28:35.714
- Or something.
- I'll let you in on a secret.

28:35.757 --> 28:38.325
Deep down, Hana digsthe attention I give her.

28:38.368 --> 28:39.892
- No.
[chuckles]

28:39.935 --> 28:42.242
- Okay, you lay a finger on me,and I got 12 witnesses here.

28:42.285 --> 28:44.679
You'll be run out of the bureaufaster than I was.

28:44.723 --> 28:46.202
- Kenny, forget him.

28:46.246 --> 28:49.379
[soft dramatic music]

28:49.423 --> 28:51.904
- Already have.

28:51.947 --> 28:54.036
♪

28:54.080 --> 28:56.865
- So, bottom line, you're
no closer to catching him?

28:56.909 --> 28:58.127
I want Carly away from this.

28:58.171 --> 29:00.086
I'm taking herto JFK this afternoon.

29:00.129 --> 29:01.740
She's catching a flightto San Francisco.

29:01.783 --> 29:03.524
You can't stop mefrom protecting her.

29:03.567 --> 29:05.004
- We're protecting her here.

29:05.047 --> 29:06.527
- We just need to get onwith our lives.

29:06.570 --> 29:08.616
- Stop trying to decide
what works for us.

29:08.659 --> 29:11.575
- All right, we'll notifythe San Francisco office.

29:11.619 --> 29:13.229
Have them provide you
with security.

29:13.273 --> 29:14.796
What's your plan?

29:14.840 --> 29:16.667
- I'm gonna stay heretill you catch this piece of--

29:16.711 --> 29:18.408
♪

29:18.452 --> 29:20.410
- Are you sure you wouldn'trather be with your wife?

29:20.454 --> 29:23.849
- She's safer without me.

29:23.892 --> 29:25.633
It's me he wants.

29:25.676 --> 29:32.596
♪

29:35.774 --> 29:36.949
- Double double
with double everything.

29:36.992 --> 29:38.341
- Mm, thanks.

29:38.385 --> 29:40.517
That Wellman, he's a pieceof work, huh?

29:40.561 --> 29:42.606
- One of God's little mistakes.

29:43.694 --> 29:45.784
- I recovered
Fallon's search history.

29:45.827 --> 29:49.439
Before he disappeared,he was cruising AirBnB,

29:49.483 --> 29:51.615
looking at housesin Central New Jersey.

29:51.659 --> 29:53.095
- He's looking
for an empty house.

29:53.139 --> 29:54.618
- Did he find one?

29:54.662 --> 29:57.360
- All I have is his searchhistory, no transactions,

29:57.404 --> 30:00.276
but let me look and seewhat else I can recover.

30:00.320 --> 30:03.453
[phone ringing]

30:05.020 --> 30:07.501
- LaCroix.

30:07.544 --> 30:09.242
Check the security video.

30:09.285 --> 30:11.722
Don't let Ms. Thompson
board that flight.

30:11.766 --> 30:12.985
♪

30:13.028 --> 30:14.943
Chris Thompson gave
the slip to the security

30:14.987 --> 30:16.858
after they dropped his wife off
at the airport.

30:16.902 --> 30:19.774
[dramatic music]

30:19.818 --> 30:21.471
[sighs]

30:25.954 --> 30:28.348
- I had no idea
he would do this.

30:28.391 --> 30:30.785
He was frustrated.We both were.

30:30.829 --> 30:32.526
But I never would'veagreed to it.

30:32.569 --> 30:33.657
[soft dramatic music]

30:33.701 --> 30:36.878
Chris can't take onthis monster.

30:36.922 --> 30:38.662
- Does he own a gun?

30:38.706 --> 30:40.577
- He borrowed one
from his brother

30:40.621 --> 30:42.841
when we started
getting harassed.

30:42.884 --> 30:44.712
- How would your husband
find Fallon?

30:44.755 --> 30:46.366
Was he in contact with him?

30:46.409 --> 30:48.585
- When Chris startedgetting emails from Fallon,

30:48.629 --> 30:51.675
he would write back, you know,begging him to leave us alone,

30:51.719 --> 30:53.155
and, sometimes,we'd get a reply,

30:53.199 --> 30:54.765
but that was months ago.

30:54.809 --> 30:56.680
- The trackers we have
on their devices

30:56.724 --> 30:58.682
don't show
any unusual activity.

30:58.726 --> 31:00.902
- Your husband wouldn't have

31:00.946 --> 31:02.251
another phone he didn't
tell us about, would he?

31:02.295 --> 31:04.775
- No.

31:04.819 --> 31:08.954
But yesterday morning,he went into the office.

31:09.737 --> 31:12.348
He said he had projecthe absolutely had to finish.

31:12.392 --> 31:14.263
One of the agentswent with him.

31:14.307 --> 31:15.874
- His work computer.

31:15.917 --> 31:17.788
- Check the assistant'scomputer too.

31:17.832 --> 31:19.965
- On it.

31:21.401 --> 31:22.489
- [sighs]

31:22.532 --> 31:27.450
♪

31:27.494 --> 31:29.496
- We're coming up on it
on the right--

31:29.539 --> 31:31.846
right there past the barrier.

31:31.890 --> 31:38.461
♪

31:38.505 --> 31:40.681
- Charming.

31:40.724 --> 31:42.509
- Fallon's email said he put
a burner phone for Thompson

31:42.552 --> 31:44.641
in a chicken bucket.

31:44.685 --> 31:47.166
- What's that for?
- Rats.

31:47.209 --> 31:54.347
♪

31:55.478 --> 31:57.567
- We got fresh tire tracks
over here!

31:57.611 --> 32:02.572
♪

32:02.616 --> 32:04.400
- Chicken bucket over here!

32:04.444 --> 32:06.228
Full of grease
but no burner phone--

32:06.272 --> 32:07.490
Thompson must have
picked it up.

32:07.534 --> 32:08.970
- Check the nearest cell tower.

32:09.014 --> 32:10.580
Maybe he used the phone
right away.

32:10.624 --> 32:15.672
♪

32:15.716 --> 32:18.327
- Got it--prepaid burner
used 30 minutes ago

32:18.371 --> 32:20.503
heading south on Route 206.

32:20.547 --> 32:23.202
♪

32:23.245 --> 32:25.073
He's got 15 miles on us.

32:25.117 --> 32:26.901
- Call him up for me.

32:26.945 --> 32:28.511
♪

32:28.555 --> 32:29.556
- Here you go.

32:29.599 --> 32:32.515
♪

32:32.559 --> 32:37.172
[phone ringing]

32:37.216 --> 32:38.434
- Fallon?

32:38.478 --> 32:40.393
- Mr. Thompson,
it's Agent LaCroix.

32:40.436 --> 32:42.569
I'd like you to pull over
so we can talk to you.

32:42.612 --> 32:45.137
- No, this ends now,
whatever it takes.

32:45.180 --> 32:47.008
- This man has
already killed two people.

32:47.052 --> 32:49.271
You're walking into a trap.
- My life's a trap.

32:49.315 --> 32:50.707
I won't live like this.

32:50.751 --> 32:52.187
- I'd like you to think
of your wife and child.

32:52.231 --> 32:54.363
You're no good to them dead
or in prison.

32:54.407 --> 32:55.886
- I'm no good to them now.

32:55.930 --> 32:58.889
If I don't have the guts
to protect them, what use am I?

32:58.933 --> 33:00.587
[phone beeps]

33:00.630 --> 33:02.719
- He hung up.

33:02.763 --> 33:04.373
- He's only ten miles
ahead of us now.

33:04.417 --> 33:07.550
He just turned down Route 518.

33:07.594 --> 33:08.595
- Punch it.

33:08.638 --> 33:14.993
♪

33:15.036 --> 33:16.037
[tires screeching]

33:16.081 --> 33:23.044
♪

33:25.829 --> 33:27.353
- Burner phone's on the floor.

33:27.396 --> 33:29.833
♪

33:29.877 --> 33:31.966
- There's fresh blood up here.

33:32.010 --> 33:34.012
♪

33:34.055 --> 33:37.537
- Drag marks along the ground,
tire tracks.

33:37.580 --> 33:39.147
Fallon took him.

33:39.191 --> 33:43.760
♪

33:43.804 --> 33:45.980
- The AirBnB houses
Fallon was looking at

33:46.024 --> 33:48.069
are all over
Central New Jersey.

33:48.113 --> 33:50.463
- Start within ten milesof where he snatched Thompson,

33:50.506 --> 33:54.423
towns like Hopewell, Mt. Rose.

33:54.467 --> 33:56.599
And checkwith AirBnB transactions.

33:56.643 --> 33:59.428
- Jess, take a look
at this house.

33:59.472 --> 34:01.256
The well in the front yard

34:01.300 --> 34:03.476
is the same as the house
with the neighborhood bully--

34:03.519 --> 34:05.869
a two-story house
with shutters.

34:05.913 --> 34:08.176
- Just like the scene
of Fallon's first humiliation.

34:08.220 --> 34:09.395
She's right.

34:09.438 --> 34:10.396
This is where
he'd take Thompson.

34:10.439 --> 34:13.877
♪

34:13.921 --> 34:16.489
- [sobs]

34:16.532 --> 34:19.231
Mr. Fallon, please,
let me explain.

34:19.274 --> 34:21.102
- It's too late for that.

34:21.146 --> 34:24.540
- I know I was rude,but my wife was in pain.

34:24.584 --> 34:25.628
- Oh, there we go.

34:25.672 --> 34:27.326
It's alwayssomeone else's fault.

34:27.369 --> 34:29.154
[ominous music]

34:29.197 --> 34:31.373
Do you think you'remore important than me?

34:31.417 --> 34:33.419
- What?
No.

34:33.462 --> 34:35.116
Please, I'm trying
to apologize.

34:35.160 --> 34:38.424
- [laughs]Apolo--you brought a gun!

34:38.467 --> 34:41.383
♪

34:41.427 --> 34:42.993
You obviously needto learn manners.

34:43.037 --> 34:44.169
Just--
- [muffled scream]

34:44.212 --> 34:45.692
- Yeah, shh.

34:45.735 --> 34:48.695
- [muffled whimpering]

34:48.738 --> 34:55.876
♪

35:01.360 --> 35:03.492
- Lesson one.

35:03.536 --> 35:04.972
- [muffled scream]

35:09.368 --> 35:12.327
[suspenseful music]

35:12.371 --> 35:19.247
♪

35:28.343 --> 35:31.041
- Clear!
- Clear!

35:31.085 --> 35:32.042
♪

35:32.086 --> 35:34.175
- Clear!

35:34.219 --> 35:36.134
- Clear front!

35:36.177 --> 35:38.310
- Clear.

35:38.353 --> 35:39.746
[indistinct radio chatter]

35:39.789 --> 35:42.879
- No sign Fallon's been here.
- It seemed perfect.

35:42.923 --> 35:45.447
♪

35:45.491 --> 35:48.711
- It is perfect,
but he didn't wanna be in it.

35:48.755 --> 35:51.497
He wanted to see it
just like when he was a kid--

35:51.540 --> 35:52.889
from across the street.

35:52.933 --> 35:55.979
You see that house
with the "for sale" sign?

35:56.023 --> 35:58.373
Basement window on the right.

35:58.417 --> 36:01.246
That's where he is.

36:01.289 --> 36:03.378
- Now that's how youstand up for yourself.

36:03.422 --> 36:06.512
Nobody slaps me in the faceand gets away with it.

36:06.555 --> 36:09.732
I would've made that bastardeat his taillight.

36:09.776 --> 36:12.692
[suspenseful music]

36:12.735 --> 36:19.742
♪

36:19.786 --> 36:20.961
Come on, move it.

36:21.004 --> 36:23.006
♪

36:23.050 --> 36:24.921
[both grunting]
Come on!

36:24.965 --> 36:26.184
- [screams]

36:26.227 --> 36:28.055
- Stop right there.Stop right there.

36:28.098 --> 36:29.665
♪

36:29.709 --> 36:32.929
Back off!Back off!

36:32.973 --> 36:36.977
♪

36:37.020 --> 36:39.371
- What's the plan, David?

36:41.199 --> 36:43.070
- I'm going outthat door to the garage,

36:43.113 --> 36:45.333
I'm taking him with me,and I'm driving away.

36:45.377 --> 36:46.813
- And then what?

36:46.856 --> 36:49.207
- I don't owe you an answer,so just get out of the way!

36:49.250 --> 36:50.556
- We know why
you chose this house.

36:50.599 --> 36:51.861
We know the whole story.

36:51.905 --> 36:53.472
- We even met your neighbor.

36:53.515 --> 36:54.777
♪

36:54.821 --> 36:57.215
- He's a real sorry excuse
for a human being.

36:57.258 --> 36:59.260
- Right?So you know.

36:59.304 --> 37:00.870
You saw.

37:00.914 --> 37:03.525
♪

37:03.569 --> 37:07.268
- I read your journal, David--
your diary.

37:07.312 --> 37:10.228
I can sympathize with
what you've been through.

37:10.271 --> 37:11.316
- Yeah?

37:11.359 --> 37:13.796
Well, this one,he's one of those,

37:13.840 --> 37:15.885
so just let me dowhat I got to do.

37:15.929 --> 37:22.892
♪

37:22.936 --> 37:24.546
- I can't let you
leave with him.

37:24.590 --> 37:25.678
♪

37:25.721 --> 37:27.593
But I think
you've made your point.

37:27.636 --> 37:30.422
You righted the wrong,
you know what I mean?

37:30.465 --> 37:32.032
What happened
to your father?

37:32.075 --> 37:37.080
♪

37:37.124 --> 37:39.300
- My dad was a coward.

37:39.344 --> 37:42.260
He should've fought back,but he just took it.

37:42.303 --> 37:44.566
- I don't think your father
was a coward.

37:44.610 --> 37:47.090
He had a disease.
He had depression.

37:47.134 --> 37:49.049
- What are you--What are you talking about?

37:49.092 --> 37:51.051
He--I saw him with my own eyes.

37:51.094 --> 37:52.748
He let that guybitch slap him.

37:52.792 --> 37:55.534
♪

37:55.577 --> 37:57.579
- David, I want
to show you something

37:57.623 --> 37:59.320
Okay?

37:59.364 --> 38:01.453
- What are you doing?
- Just give me a second.

38:01.496 --> 38:03.716
I want to show you
your father's autopsy report.

38:03.759 --> 38:07.110
You need to see it.
You owe it to yourself.

38:07.154 --> 38:08.547
Okay, just take a look at it.

38:08.590 --> 38:09.939
- No, I don't wanna see it.
- Take a look, David.

38:09.983 --> 38:10.897
- I don't wanna look at it.

38:10.940 --> 38:13.160
♪

38:13.203 --> 38:15.205
- It says that your father
took his own life.

38:15.249 --> 38:17.947
♪

38:17.991 --> 38:19.906
- What?No.

38:19.949 --> 38:21.299
- Not because of your neighbor

38:21.342 --> 38:23.301
or because of your mother
or because of you,

38:23.344 --> 38:26.260
but because he was in pain.

38:26.304 --> 38:28.349
Your father was
a very sick man,

38:28.393 --> 38:30.046
but he wasn't a coward.

38:30.090 --> 38:31.570
He worked every day.

38:31.613 --> 38:33.789
He provided for you,
for your mother.

38:33.833 --> 38:35.138
He did the best he could.

38:35.182 --> 38:36.705
♪

38:36.749 --> 38:38.925
- [crying]

38:38.968 --> 38:40.535
♪

38:40.579 --> 38:43.669
- You don't need to be
angry at him anymore.

38:43.712 --> 38:50.719
♪

38:50.763 --> 38:54.506
- Oh, God.[sobbing]

38:54.549 --> 39:00.816
♪

39:00.860 --> 39:03.253
- You can let go now, David.

39:03.297 --> 39:04.907
♪

39:04.951 --> 39:07.301
No need to punish
anybody anymore.

39:07.345 --> 39:09.956
- [panting and sobbing]

39:09.999 --> 39:12.959
♪

39:13.002 --> 39:15.614
- I got you.

39:15.657 --> 39:20.183
♪

39:20.227 --> 39:22.011
- Take him up.

39:22.055 --> 39:26.189
♪

39:26.233 --> 39:28.017
Good one, boss.

39:28.061 --> 39:29.367
♪

39:29.410 --> 39:31.543
- It was touch and go there
for a while.

39:31.586 --> 39:34.676
♪

39:34.720 --> 39:38.114
- You always do that.
Always empathize with them,

39:38.158 --> 39:41.074
try to make them feel better
about themselves.

39:41.117 --> 39:44.120
Why?

39:44.164 --> 39:46.384
♪

39:46.427 --> 39:49.256
- So they know
they have a choice.

39:49.299 --> 39:56.394
♪

39:57.438 --> 39:59.484
[indistinct chatter]

40:03.444 --> 40:07.013
- I saw you caught Fallon.Better late than never.

40:07.056 --> 40:08.536
So you called to tellme you're ready

40:08.580 --> 40:10.451
to move our thing forward?
- Yes.

40:10.495 --> 40:13.280
I'm moving forward.
- I knew you'd come around.

40:13.323 --> 40:14.455
So I was thinking,we could go tonight--

40:14.499 --> 40:16.152
- There's no "we" here.

40:16.196 --> 40:19.286
I'm moving forward
right past you.

40:19.329 --> 40:21.984
You told my buddy the other day
that you think

40:22.028 --> 40:23.551
I secretly dig your attention,

40:23.595 --> 40:26.032
which made me realize
that you've been operating

40:26.075 --> 40:27.512
in the dark--

40:27.555 --> 40:29.557
that you have
no concept of what

40:29.601 --> 40:31.211
your attention has done to me,

40:31.254 --> 40:33.387
the impact
that it's had on my life.

40:33.431 --> 40:36.259
- Hana, I know--
- No, you don't know.

40:36.303 --> 40:39.219
So now you need to hear me.

40:39.262 --> 40:42.048
After our one date,

40:42.091 --> 40:44.442
after a month of
your constant attention,

40:44.485 --> 40:46.269
your texts and emails

40:46.313 --> 40:48.881
and buzzing my apartment
day and night,

40:48.924 --> 40:51.231
I started having migraines.

40:51.274 --> 40:53.320
I get nauseous,
sick to my stomach,

40:53.363 --> 40:55.496
just to see an email
in my inbox from you.

40:55.540 --> 40:58.586
And three months later,
I had an outbreak of eczema.

40:58.630 --> 41:01.110
I hadn't had eczema
since I was eight.

41:01.154 --> 41:04.200
And then my period stopped.

41:04.244 --> 41:06.289
The doctor said
it was all stress-related.

41:06.333 --> 41:09.597
Here, I brought
the doctor's bills

41:09.641 --> 41:11.338
in case you don't believe me.

41:11.381 --> 41:13.253
I was diagnosed
with anxiety disorder.

41:13.296 --> 41:15.124
I had to go on medication.

41:15.168 --> 41:17.344
I saw three
different therapists.

41:17.387 --> 41:20.129
♪

41:20.173 --> 41:21.827
I was afraid.

41:21.870 --> 41:23.350
♪

41:23.393 --> 41:25.439
I carry a gun,

41:25.483 --> 41:28.050
and I was afraid
all the time,

41:28.094 --> 41:29.574
because you made me afraid.

41:29.617 --> 41:31.401
